    "body": "This reverts #38869\r\n\r\nAI-assisted: Codex\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n`vim.pos` and `vim.range` expose tables that act both as classes and as the module return value. The doc generator treated all class members as class methods, so functions defined with `.` were rendered like `Pos:to_extmark()` and `Range:has()`.\r\n\r\nBut these functions are meant to be documented as module functions, with module tags such as\r\n`vim.pos.to_extmark()` and `vim.range.has()`, while only `:`-defined members should remain class methods.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nRecord whether a class member was declared with `.` or `:` in the LuaCATS parser, and use that information in `gen_vimdoc.lua` when rendering helptags, signatures, and generated class fields.\r\n\r\nFor class tables that are also the module return value:\r\n- `.`-defined members are rendered as module functions with short signatures and full module tags, and excluded from generated class field lists.\r\n- `:`-defined members keep their existing class-method rendering.\r\n",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-16T09:42:34Z",
